# Magic Item Crafting

Anyone can swing a sword. Adventurers master enchanted blades that burn with elemental fury. The difference? Someone crafted that magic—invested Flow, gathered materials, and bound supernatural power into mundane metal. Magic item crafting transforms you from consumer of magical treasures to creator of them.

{% if crafting_data and crafting_data.description %}{{ crafting_data.description }}{% else %}Crafting magical items requires knowledge, materials, time, and most importantly: Flow investment. You pour your own magical energy into the creation across days, weeks, or months. The result is permanent enchantment that persists indefinitely.{% endif %}

This system lets wizards create scrolls for emergency casting, artificers enchant party equipment, and late-game characters craft legendary artifacts. Crafting isn't quick or cheap—but it provides access to exactly the magic items you need rather than hoping random treasure provides them.

