## Crafting Requirements

### Knowledge Prerequisites

You cannot create magical effects you don't understand:

**Spell-Based Items:** Must know the spell you're imbuing (potions, scrolls, wands)
**Enhancement Items:** Must have Craft skill appropriate to base item type
**Unique Properties:** Requires GM collaboration to define effect and requirements

Cannot create Healing Potion without knowing Heal spell. Cannot enchant weapon without Weaponsmith or similar craft expertise. The magic binds to your understanding—without knowledge, binding fails.

### Material Components

Magic items require special materials beyond mundane crafting supplies:

**Consumables (Potions/Scrolls):** Rare inks, alchemical reagents, spell focuses
**Permanent Items:** Magical essences, gemstones, enchanted metals
**Legendary Items:** Unique materials (dragon scales, celestial metals, artifacts)

